Package: razzo
Type: Package
Title: The Error if Nature is MBD
Version: 0.8.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Giovanni", "Laudanno", role = c("aut")),
    person("Richel J.C.", "Bilderbeek", email = "richel@richelbilderbeek.nl", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1107-7049")))
Maintainer: Richel J.C. Bilderbeek <richel@richelbilderbeek.nl>
Description: The MBD (Multiple-Birth-Death) model is a model in which
    speciation events can happen at exactly the same time.
    Contemporary standard phylogenetic tools ignore this feature of nature.
    This package measures the error BEAST2 makes if nature follow that model,
    when we are only using contemporary priors.
